Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.34,0:01:12.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历史频道 - 宇宙 第4季第4集 爆炸之最\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The History Channel - The Universe s04e04 Biggest Blasts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.53,0:01:15.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们不仅能在弹指一挥间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can not only wipe out cities
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.53,0:01:18.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抹去我们数以百万计人口的城市\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}filled with millions of people in the blink of an eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.03,0:01:25.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且还能毁灭整个大陆 行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but can lay waste to entire continents, planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.87,0:01:28.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至撕裂星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and even rip galaxies apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.71,0:01:34.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间到处都是剧烈的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The universe is filled with tremendously violent explosions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.42,0:01:36.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸和事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and blasts and events.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.93,0:01:41.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,祥和的地球生活\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The calm serenity of life on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.97,0:01:45.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一定程度上 是个例外 而不是常态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is, to some degree, the exception, not the norm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.81,0:01:53.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们不管是大规模碰撞还是整个恒星的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And whether they're massive collisions or explosions of entire stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.23,0:01:56.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其要素大同小异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they all have important elements in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.65,0:02:00.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,确实 换句话说 爆发或爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Really, another way to say explosion or blast
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:02.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是能量的同时大释放\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is just a big liberation of energy all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:07.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你从已具结构的对象中释放大量的能量时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you liberate a lot of energy in something that already has structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.75,0:02:12.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,往往会破坏该结构 因此看上去极具破坏性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you tend to demolish the structure, so that seems very destructive,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.25,0:02:15.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是自然规律会攫取能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the laws of nature will take energy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.30,0:02:18.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并将其改造成一些其它的形式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and reconstruct it into some other form.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.59,0:02:27.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1994年 苏梅克-列维九号彗星的20多块碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1994, more than 20 pieces of the Shoemaker-Levy 9 comet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.31,0:02:28.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,痛击了木星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pummeled Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.95,0:02:42.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大黑疤横跨木星表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were big black scars all across the face of Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:45.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,疤痕之大连业余望远镜都一目了然\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so large even that they could be seen clearly even with amateur telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.12,0:02:51.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最大的彗星碎片超过了1英里宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The largest comet fragment was more than a mile wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.29,0:02:57.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其冲击力相当于600万兆吨TNT\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the force of its impact was equal to 6 million megatons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.80,0:03:03.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约是世界全部核武器的100倍还不止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's about a hundred times or more of the entire nuclear arsenal of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.51,0:03:07.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你在地球的每一个角落都放上一个炸弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you took every bomb in every corner on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.60,0:03:09.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时爆炸成为一个大爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and exploded it in one big explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.81,0:03:15.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都比不上这个碎片撞击木星所产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you wouldn't even begin to touch the power of this fragment colliding into Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.03,0:03:25.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是猜猜看 即使是此类能量都不够格\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But guess what? Even that type of power isn't enough to qualify
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.16,0:03:28.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为宇宙间最大的爆炸之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as one of the biggest blasts in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.75,0:03:36.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入前10位的第一个项目具有N多倍的破坏性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The first event to make the top 10 was many times more devastating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:40.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第10 - 死神从天而降
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.51,0:03:46.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们名录上最小的爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The smallest blast on our list
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:49.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能还是大得足以抹去恐龙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may still have been big enough to wipe out the dinosaurs
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.77,0:03:52.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为其烟雾和碎片遮挡了阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by blocking out the Sun with smoke and debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.61,0:03:58.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是希克苏鲁伯撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the Chicxulub impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.61,0:04:01.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约6500万年前 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the asteroid that crashed into Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.08,0:04:04.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星撞击墨西哥尤卡坦半岛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 65 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.03,0:04:09.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一块6英里宽的太空石头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A 6-mile-wide space rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.41,0:04:12.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大过珠峰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}taller than Mount Everest and almost as wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.41,0:04:13.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,闯入地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thundered into Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:24.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我现在坐在亚利桑那州流星陨石坑前面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So I'm sitting in front of Meteor Crater in Arizona,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.13,0:04:26.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它约四分之三英里宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is about 3/4 of a mile wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:28.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们开车跨越它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if we were to drive across this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.72,0:04:32.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时速55到60迈 会要用上一分钟时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at about 55 or 60 miles per hour, it would take, like, a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:37.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞击尤卡坦半岛的小行星所创造出来的弹坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the crater created by the asteroid that impacted the Yucatan Peninsula,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.90,0:04:40.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驱车以同样的速度跨越 需要两个多小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would take over two hours to drive it at about the same speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.03,0:04:44.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你可以想象那个弹坑比我身后的这个要大多少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you can imagine how much larger that crater is than this one behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.20,0:04:52.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径112英里的弹坑大到足以放下纽约市\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The 112-mile-diameter crater is big enough to fit New York City,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.20,0:04:56.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,费城 以及两者之间的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Philadelphia, and everything in between inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:05:01.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假如撞击发生在今天 约有1200万人会当场毙命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it struck today, about 12 million people would be killed instantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.13,0:05:05.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更不用提弹坑扩散所造成的破坏和伤亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not to mention the damage and casualties that would spread beyond the crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.97,0:05:11.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为每一个爆炸的能量释放有几个途径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's because the energy in every blast is released in several ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.56,0:05:14.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,例如撞击时的致盲闪光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as light during the blinding flash of the impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:21.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热量 能够将野火蔓延至全球大部分地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and heat, capable of spreading wildfires across much of the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.36,0:05:24.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过伴随撞击的 大部分破坏来自\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But with collisions, most of the devastation comes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.24,0:05:27.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,运动的能量 所谓的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the energy of motion, known as kinetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.57,0:05:30.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生弹坑 飞出碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which creates the crater and the flying debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.91,0:05:39.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,创造希克苏鲁伯陨石坑的撞击所产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy in the impact that created the crater at Chicxulub
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.54,0:05:44.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必定是十分巨大的 或许有2 5亿兆吨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had to have been enormous, probably about 250 million megatons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.76,0:05:46.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.59,0:05:51.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球史上爆炸的最大炸弹是50兆吨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The largest bomb ever exploded on Earth was 50 megatons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:59.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那对比2 5亿可以给你去判断\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that compared to 250 million gives you a sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.15,0:06:03.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是击中木星的苏梅克-列维九号彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was also about 40 times greater than the energy released
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.40,0:06:07.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最大的碎片所释放能量的40倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the largest Shoemaker-Levy 9 comet fragment to hit Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:13.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,计算一颗庞大小行星撞击所释放的动能的过程中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In figuring out the kinetic energy released in a huge asteroid impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.62,0:06:16.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要命的是将某些非常庞大的数字\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's all a matter of plugging some very big numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.33,0:06:19.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,插入一个简单的方程式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a simple equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.21,0:06:21.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,考虑这种碰撞的能量时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The key thing to keep in mind 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.45,0:06:23.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要记住的关键之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when considering the energy in these kinds of collisions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:26.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在于所谓的动能方程式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that the formula for what's called the kinetic energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.84,0:06:29.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动能等于1/2 [M × V 的平方]\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the energy of motion, is 1/2 [M x V squared],
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.88,0:06:32.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量乘以速度的平方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mass and then the square of the velocities.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.68,0:06:36.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量就是物体的重量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mass is the weight of the object,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.52,0:06:39.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,速度是其运动的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and velocity is the speed it's traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.35,0:06:42.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的能量可以来自\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can have a huge amount of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.52,0:06:45.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,够重或够快的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a massive enough or fast enough object.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.86,0:06:49.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,考虑到希克苏鲁伯小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Considering that the Chicxulub asteroid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:52.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重如珠峰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}weighed nearly as much as Mount Everest
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,速度超过时速5万英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and was moving at over 50,000 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.04,0:06:59.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约是手枪子弹速度的50倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 50 times faster than a bullet from a revolver,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:03.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难怪它是宇宙间最大的爆炸之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's no wonder it was one of the biggest blasts in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.34,0:07:13.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它对整个地球结构的影响又当如何呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what about its effect on the structure of the entire planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:23.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆破专家把一小块炸药放在西瓜皮的下面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An explosives expert places a small charge just under the skin of a watermelon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.31,0:07:28.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来模拟这颗小行星撞上地球时能量释放的类型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to simulate the type of energy released when this asteroid slammed into Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.62,0:07:40.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以看到 伤害我们的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As you can see, something that would be devastating to us 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:45.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是不会太伤及整个地球的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not too devastating to the planet as a whole,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:51.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以还是有相当大的空间来对付更大的爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's still plenty of room for the blasts to get bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.21,0:07:55.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第9 - 火星撞击
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:02.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是 火星而非地球成了一颗小行星的靶子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Luckily, Mars and not Earth was the target of an asteroid
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:07.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它比撞上尤卡坦半岛的小行星大了200倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}200 times larger than the one that slammed into the Yucatan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.07,0:08:15.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,39亿年前撞上火星的小行星有1200英里宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The asteroid that impacted Mars about 3.9 billion years ago was 1,200 miles wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.62,0:08:19.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那大约是冥王星大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, that's about the size of Pluto,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:21.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不妨想象美国大陆的大部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and if you imagine most of the continental U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:23.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从丹佛到佛罗里达的狭长地带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from Denver to the Florida panhandle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.75,0:08:27.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上至芝加哥 下至得克萨斯南部 庞大无比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Chicago down to the south of Texas, huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.13,0:08:32.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是该小行星的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's just the size of the asteroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:36.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弹坑 叫做伯勒里斯盆地 是另外一个故事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The crater, known as the Borealis Basin, is another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:40.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,坑洞覆盖了星球的40%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hole covers about 40% of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:45.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星伯勒里斯盆地宽约5300英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the Borealis Basin on Mars is about 5,300 miles wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.98,0:08:48.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我身后的弹坑只不过一英里宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the crater behind me is not even a mile wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:52.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你可以想象这个乘以5000倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you can imagine multiplying this by over 5,000 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.36,0:08:55.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是火星撞击坑的规模了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's the size of the impact crater on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:58.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那相当于非洲大陆的大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's about the size of the continent of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.74,0:09:00.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大得惊人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Amazingly huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:06.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然撞击火星的小行星的速度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While the speed of the asteroid that smacked Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.17,0:09:09.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与撞击尤卡坦半岛的那个大差不离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wasn't much different than the one that hit the Yucatan Peninsula,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:12.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是质量要大上N多倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the mass was many times greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:16.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,导致了能量释放要大上好多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leading to a much larger release of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.09,0:09:18.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量或许大上100万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's probably about a million times more energetic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.72,0:09:24.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此约是250兆兆吨的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it'd be about 250 million million megatons of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.81,0:09:26.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's a lot of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.60,0:09:29.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你会看到有这么大的一个盆地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's why you've got such a big, big basin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.07,0:09:35.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天要是那样的东西打击地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something like that hitting the Earth today
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.24,0:09:38.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞬间死亡的人数会达到数十亿之多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would put the instant death toll in the billions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.61,0:09:42.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随后会抹去地球上所有的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and would probably wipe out all life on the planet soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.21,0:09:55.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过接下来的爆炸曾炸掉过我们星球更大的一块地壳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the next blast did blow an even bigger chunk of crust off our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.38,0:09:58.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所幸是在尚未面世之前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}luckily, before life even existed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.38,0:10:03.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第8 - 大劈开
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:07.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是火星成了靶子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead of Mars being a target,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:12.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下一颗大如火星的小行星撞上了地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}imagine an asteroid the size of Mars slamming into Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.48,0:10:17.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多数行星科学家认为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most planetary scientists believe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.49,0:10:20.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是地球在46亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's exactly what happened soon after the Earth 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.70,0:10:23.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成后不久所发生的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}formed about 4.6 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.95,0:10:26.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它被称为大撞击学说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's known as the Giant Impactor Theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.91,0:10:29.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也俗称大劈开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also nicknamed the Big Splat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.00,0:10:35.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早期太阳系是个比今天热闹得多的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The early solar system was a much busier place than it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.25,0:10:37.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,基本上 它还未安顿下来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Basically, it hadn't settled down yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.22,0:10:42.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此有大量的碎片在四处乱跑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so there are lots of fragments running around,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:43.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,孳生了各种各样的碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}producing all sorts of collisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.01,0:10:48.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终导致了我们今天所知的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which ultimately produced the bodies we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:54.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球当时还是熔岩一片 聊无生机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth was still a molten wasteland, devoid of life back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:10:56.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是好事一桩 因为那次撞击的力道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is a good thing, since the force of that collision
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.98,0:10:59.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会让生命中途夭折\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have ended life in its tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.99,0:11:03.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么地球又是如何从史上最黄最暴力的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So how did the planet recover
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.95,0:11:06.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事件中恢复过来的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the most violent event in its history?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.17,0:11:17.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间许多爆炸之最\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of the biggest blasts in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:22.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是彗星和小行星撞上行星造成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are caused by comets and asteroids slamming into planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.09,0:11:25.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些撞击释放的能量可以是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These impacts can unleash hundreds of times more energy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.76,0:11:28.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球整个核武器的数百倍还多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the entire nuclear arsenal on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.81,0:11:36.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们名录上的第8号甚至比那更强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But number 8 on our list is even more powerful than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.57,0:11:41.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸的肇因是一块大如行星的石头撞上了地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A blast caused by a rock the size of a planet slamming into Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.32,0:11:45.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它实际发生在地球形成后不久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It actually happened soon after the Earth had formed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:50.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约46亿年前 当时一个大如火星的物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 4.6 billion years ago, when an object the size of Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.41,0:11:52.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时被称为忒伊亚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes known as Theia,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.62,0:11:56.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞上我们的星球 带来了灾难性的后果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}slammed into our world with catastrophic effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.30,0:12:06.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相对撞上火星的冥王星大小的小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Compared to the Pluto-sized asteroid that smashed into Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.35,0:12:08.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那块盯上地球的火星般大小的石头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Mars-sized rock that nailed Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:12.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要大上三倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was more than three times larger,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:16.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放的动能更大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}releasing much more kinetic energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.06,0:12:18.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,敲掉地球外壳的忒伊亚撞击者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Theia impactor that knocked off the crust of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.77,0:12:22.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许要比伯勒里斯盆地撞击者强大10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was probably about 10 times more powerful than the Borealis Basin impactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:29.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这个难以置信的破坏力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this incredibly destructive force
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.20,0:12:31.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也有一些很重要的好处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}also had some very important benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:35.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,忒伊亚撞上地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So when Theia impacted the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.58,0:12:38.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许发生了一次侧击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it happened probably at a glancing blow,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.13,0:12:41.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样一来 两颗行星的铁核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in doing so, the iron cores of the two planets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:47.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上就融合在了一块 形成了更大的铁核 更大的地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually melded together and formed a larger iron core and a larger Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:49.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在忒伊亚的地幔可能在撞击中完全炸飞了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now Theia's mantle probably got completely blown off
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.89,0:12:52.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它比地球小一些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this impact because it's a little smaller than Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:55.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球的部分地幔也炸飞了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and some of the Earth's mantle got blown off,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.52,0:12:59.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样你就看到这种地幔碎片漂浮在四处 转动起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you have all this mantle debris floating around, orbiting,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.27,0:13:02.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它实际上兼并在一起形成了月球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it actually coalesced to form the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.07,0:13:08.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月球稳定了地球的地轴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Moon stabilized Earth's axis,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.37,0:13:10.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,防止它倾斜失控\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}preventing it from tilting wildly,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.91,0:13:13.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而保持了地球气候的稳定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which keeps Earth's climate steady.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.17,0:13:22.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它也将地球的自转速度减缓到我们目前的昼夜24小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It also slowed Earth's rotation over time to the 24-hour days we have now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.46,0:13:26.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再来模拟这个爆炸的威力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once again, to simulate the power of this blast,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.93,0:13:31.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆破专家在代表地球的西瓜上放上炸药\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an explosives expert places a charge on a melon representing Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.10,0:13:34.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这会把西瓜炸飞吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could this be the one that blows the melon away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.11,0:13:46.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管有很大的破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though there's a lot of damage,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.78,0:13:49.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,基本结构还是完好无损\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the basic structure is still intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:51.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于撞击产生的高温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With the heat of the impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:54.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球和碎片都熔化了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth and the debris were both molten.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.33,0:13:57.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那种熔化状态就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that molten state is the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:00.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞击没有留下巨大的撞击坑的原因所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why the impact didn't leave a massive crater behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.46,0:14:05.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熔化的地球重新形成球状并最终冷却了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The molten Earth re-formed as a sphere and eventually cooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:10.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么有无某种撞击可以将行星化为尘埃呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So is there any kind of impact that can turn a planet into dust?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.63,0:14:13.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第7 - 星球对撞
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.43,0:14:18.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空深处 两颗行星 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Deep in space, two planets--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.39,0:14:20.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗大如金星 另一颗 大如地球 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one the size of Venus, the other, Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.65,0:14:22.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行将对撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are on a collision course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:26.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是石质行星 没准生存着生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're rocky planets, possibly even harboring life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:27.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的太阳系里有东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something in their solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.99,0:14:30.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将它们拽出正常的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has pulled them out of their regular orbits,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是侧击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and instead of a glancing blow,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.49,0:14:34.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们可是迎头相撞在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they smash together in a head-on collision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.00,0:14:37.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些行星上的任何一个人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Anyone standing on those planets
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.66,0:14:40.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都将目睹到恐怖的事件\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have witnessed a terrifying event.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:43.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以设想一下 你直接看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can imagine, if you had a direct view
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.75,0:14:46.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有行星直奔我们而来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the planet moving toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.05,0:14:49.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着天空很快就会完全被\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means the sky would quickly fill completely
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:51.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗行将撞上的行星所覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with this planet about to impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.34,0:14:52.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是它会那样在天上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then it would be over like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会迅速消灭生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be such a rapid extinction of life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.85,0:14:59.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你或许就没时间去考虑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you probably wouldn't have time to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:06.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那不是某些虚构的末日场景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This isn't some fictional doomsday scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.03,0:15:09.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些研究者认为这种大规模的爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some researchers think this massive blast
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.86,0:15:13.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的数百年里震撼过宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rocked the cosmos within the last thousand years
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.87,0:15:17.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发生在300光年外的一个双星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a binary star system about 300 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.66,0:15:24.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是白羊座里的BD + 20-307\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's known as BD + 20-307 in the constellation Aries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:30.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有大量的尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has a tremendous amount of dust in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.59,0:15:34.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尘埃量比我们太阳系多100万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a million times more dust than in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.80,0:15:37.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为这种尘埃的产生可能源自\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think that this dust may have been produced
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.93,0:15:42.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两颗大如地球和金星的行星的撞击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the collision of two planets roughly the size of the Earth and Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.06,0:15:44.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迎面相撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just head-on, whack!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.19,0:15:51.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各自粉身碎骨 产生出大量的尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shattering each other, producing a tremendous amount of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.24,0:15:57.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要大量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It takes enormous amounts of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.83,0:16:00.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将两颗行星都粉碎至尘埃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for two planets to pulverize each other into dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:03.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在已不是地球核武器的数百倍了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now instead of hundreds of times the world's nuclear arsenal,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.83,0:16:07.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们讨论的是那个能量的数百万倍乃至数十亿倍了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're talking millions of times or even billions of times that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:09.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用上更大的炸药了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With this even larger charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.09,0:16:11.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不只是要炸掉这西瓜的一块\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're not just going to break off a chunk of this melon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.38,0:16:12.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们要将它炸得粉身碎骨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're going to blow it to smithereens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.90,0:16:37.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管行星碰撞可以是恐怖和毁灭性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as terrifying and destructive as planetary collisions can be,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.70,0:16:41.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它们还是远远小于恒星所产生的各种爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're still much smaller than the different types of blasts that come from stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.71,0:16:47.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是不可同日而语的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a whole new ballgame.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.33,0:16:50.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其主要原因就在于恒星的质量远大于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The main reason is that there's a lot more mass in a star
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.38,0:16:52.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何一颗行星规模的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than any planet-sized object,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.01,0:16:54.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是 存在着各种机制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then, there are all kinds of mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.01,0:16:58.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以发生在核聚变中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can take place involving nuclear fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.14,0:17:01.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力塌缩的各个过程中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}various processes that involve gravitational collapse,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.22,0:17:03.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也可以产生出大量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which can derive a lot of energy as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.56,0:17:12.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些高能爆炸之一就是我们名录上的第6号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of these energetic blasts is number 6 on our list.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.56,0:17:15.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第6 - 磁星爆发
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:19.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星是快速旋转的中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Magnetars are rapidly spinning neutron stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.58,0:17:22.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其形成是比我们太阳大数倍的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which form when stars several times larger than our Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.91,0:17:26.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,垂死并自我垮塌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}begin to die and collapse in upon themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.34,0:17:34.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下 如果我们的86 5万英里宽的太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine if our 865,000-mile-wide Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.09,0:17:36.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,突然被压缩成12英里长的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}suddenly compacted to the 12-mile length
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.84,0:17:38.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼哈顿岛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the island of Manhattan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.01,0:17:43.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有的物质都被压缩成非常致密的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of that matter is condensed into something so dense,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.89,0:17:48.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,估计比钢铁要坚固100百亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's estimated to be 10 billion times stronger than steel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.48,0:17:52.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了让你有概念 中子星材料有多致密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To give you an idea of how incredibly dense neutron star material is,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:55.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这盖子里装的是中子星材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if this cap was filled with neutron star stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.69,0:17:58.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在地球上会重达1000亿吨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would weigh 100 billion tons on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:18:01.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远超过此山 差不多是整个山脉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more than this hill, as much as an entire mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:09.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星名字的由来是基于这样一个事实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetar name comes from the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.71,0:18:13.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某些中子星 其原因尚且不明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that certain neutron stars, for reasons that are still unknown,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.71,0:18:17.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,具有宇宙间最强的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have the strongest magnetic fields in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:24.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星的磁场异常强烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic field of a magnetar is exceptionally strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.97,0:18:30.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可以是地球磁场的1000兆倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can be 1,000 trillion times as strong as Earth's magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.10,0:18:31.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真是了不得\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.44,0:18:34.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁场之强烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnetic fields are so intense
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:36.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是有一颗磁星突然出现在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that if a magnetar suddenly appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.78,0:18:38.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球与月球之间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}halfway between the Earth and the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.90,0:18:40.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会强烈到足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be strong enough
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:43.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,破坏地球上所有的电子设备\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to disrupt all of the electronic equipment on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.45,0:18:47.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括抹去地球上所有信用卡上的信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including stripping the information off every credit card on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.33,0:18:52.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星爆发异常强劲的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the reason magnetar flares are so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.33,0:18:55.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在于磁星特定区域周围的磁场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that the magnetic fields around certain areas of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.80,0:18:57.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时会自我扭曲得非常厉害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes twist themselves so much
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:19:03.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到它们无法再进一步扭曲了 然后突然像弹簧那样松开了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they can't twist any more, and suddenly release like a spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.47,0:19:07.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过程类似于太阳耀斑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The process is similar to a solar flare
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.68,0:19:11.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为就是磁场源源不断把能量输送上来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in that it's the magnetic field that's giving rise to the energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.27,0:19:14.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正是磁力线在各个方向不停地摆动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the shaking and tangling and sometimes the reconnection
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.61,0:19:16.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,纠缠 有时是重新连接\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of lines of force going in different directions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.78,0:19:19.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,输送能量驱动了爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that gives the energy that powers the flare.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.74,0:19:29.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而不同于行星碰撞的动能作为主导\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But unlike planetary collisions, where kinetic energy dominates,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.91,0:19:33.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁星爆发发射的大部分能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}magnetar flares shoot out most of their energy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:35.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是电磁辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as electromagnetic radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:37.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说 就是光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in other words, light.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:42.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是磁星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one magnetar flare in particular
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:48.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强大到足以在5万光年外让绕地卫星失聪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was strong enough to blind satellites orbiting Earth from 50,000 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.44,0:19:58.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙的爆炸之最\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The biggest blasts in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.48,0:20:01.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是我们在地球上能想象的东西所无法比拟的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dwarf anything we can imagine on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:05.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们已数十亿倍地超越了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're already billions of times beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.12,0:20:07.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上全部的核武器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the entire nuclear arsenal of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.25,0:20:15.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的倒数第6是耀斑爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Number 6 on our countdown are the flares that burst
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.71,0:20:20.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自极端磁化的中子星 叫做磁星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from incredibly magnetized neutron stars, known as magnetars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.84,0:20:28.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球史上观察到最强烈的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one of the most powerful ever observed from Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.10,0:20:31.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在短短的1/10秒里释放的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}released as much energy in just over a tenth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.68,0:20:35.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于我们太阳1万年里释放的总和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as our Sun does in about 100,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.81,0:20:41.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2004年里的爆发来自一颗磁星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The blast in 2004 came from a magnetar
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:47.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,叫做SGR 1806-20 在在人马座里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known as SGR 1806-20, in the constellation Sagittarius.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.78,0:20:51.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它距离地球约5万光年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's about 50,000 light-years away from Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.20,0:20:53.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在银河系的另一头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the far side of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.04,0:20:57.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的强劲令人难以置信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was incredibly powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.92,0:21:01.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有能量出自1/10秒里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All that energy came in a tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.26,0:21:06.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它冲击了刚好飞经上空的卫星探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It blasted the detectors in satellites that happened to be flying around up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.09,0:21:09.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 它是史上所见到的最亮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, it was the brightest blast ever seen
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.64,0:21:12.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳系外的天体爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from an object outside our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.56,0:21:16.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是它远在5万光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And yet it was 50,000 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.73,0:21:25.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而亮度与爆炸的威力必定有关联吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what does brightness have to do with the power of a blast?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.53,0:21:28.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我现在是在一间黑暗的房间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So I'm standing in a dark room here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.91,0:21:31.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我把灯打开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and now I'm going to turn on a light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.87,0:21:36.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,呈现给我的灯光亮度取决于两个要素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How bright that light bulb appears to me depends on two factors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.12,0:21:41.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它本质上取决于灯泡有多强或多亮 - 它的功率\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It depends on how intrinsically powerful or luminous the light bulb is--its wattage,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.71,0:21:44.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它每秒钟发出多少能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how much energy it puts out per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.17,0:21:47.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时也取决于灯泡与我的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it also depends on the distance of the light bulb from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.76,0:21:53.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我靠近灯泡 就会看到灯泡是明亮的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When I'm close to the light bulb, I see that the light bulb is bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.06,0:21:56.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我的距离增加一倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If I move a factor of two farther away,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.27,0:22:01.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么事实上 它看上去就会减弱四倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then, in fact, it looks a factor of four fainter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.23,0:22:03.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是光的平方反比定律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the inverse square law of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:06.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,灯泡的功率始终保持不变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The power of the light bulb has remained the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.65,0:22:09.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在一倍远的距离上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But by being twice as far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.11,0:22:14.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就只得到1/4的光线射到我的脸 我的眼睛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I get only 1/4 of the light reaching my face and my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.04,0:22:20.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家测量了恒星或爆发的表现亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers measure the apparent brightness of the star or the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.29,0:22:23.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们通过其它手段计算出它的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They figure out its distance through some other technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.71,0:22:26.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,根据这两个变量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And from those two variables,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.17,0:22:30.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们计算出了光源的功率或亮度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they figure out the power or the luminosity of the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:35.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所释放出来的光 不只是可见光波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That light is released, not just in visible wavelengths,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.97,0:22:38.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是整个电磁波谱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but across the electromagnetic spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.98,0:22:42.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究人员随时都在侦查伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And any time researchers detect gamma rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.19,0:22:48.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像他们对磁星爆发所做的那样知道它必定是个大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like they do in magnetar flares, they know it must be a big blast.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.24,0:22:52.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线是光的一种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gamma rays are a type of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.66,0:22:56.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是要比我们肉眼所见的光强劲N多倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but a much more energetic light than we see with our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.16,0:23:00.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们熟悉的光谱 从很低的能量开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the spectrum of light that we're familiar with goes from very low energy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.87,0:23:02.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过频谱的可见部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and through the visible part of the spectrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.00,0:23:06.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们见到的光 一直到X射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the light that we see, all the way out through x-rays
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.25,0:23:10.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入了这个光的极高能部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into this extremely high-energy component of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.63,0:23:11.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那叫做伽玛射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is called gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:23.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是1/10秒的短暂伽玛射线爆发 比如SGR 1806-20\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even a 1/10-of-a-second short gamma ray flare, like SGR 1806-20,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.48,0:23:28.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,依然能够在许多光年外用辐射来煎熬地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would still be able to fry the Earth with radiation from many light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.90,0:23:32.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要爆发的全部力道对准地球的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as long as the full force of the flare was aimed at Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.20,0:23:37.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过宇宙中并非所有的爆炸之最\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But not all of the biggest blasts in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.54,0:23:40.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是瞬间完成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are over in a fraction of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.54,0:23:44.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第6 - 亿年爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.46,0:23:52.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离地球26亿光年处 一个超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}2.6 billion light-years away from Earth, a supermassive black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.55,0:23:54.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太阳质量的数十亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of times the mass of our Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.01,0:23:59.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直横行霸道在一个星系团的中央\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been wreaking havoc in the center of a cluster of galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.89,0:24:02.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,叫做MSA 735\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Known as MSA 735,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.73,0:24:05.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它一刻不停地喷射着两束粒子流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's been shooting out two continuous jets of particles
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.52,0:24:07.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,朝着对应的两个方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in opposite directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.90,0:24:12.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认喷射已经肆虐了上亿年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists believe the jets have been raging for the past hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.49,0:24:16.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在周围的星系里冲出两个巨大的泡沫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}punching two huge bubbles into the surrounding galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.08,0:24:21.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,MSA 735 确实是黑洞吹泡泡的原型样本\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}MSA 735 really is the prototypical example of a black hole blowing bubbles.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.91,0:24:24.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们所看到的就是正被这些强大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we're seeing here is giant cavities
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.62,0:24:26.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,射流掏空的巨大的空洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}being evacuated by these powerful jets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.63,0:24:28.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们把大量的能量从黑洞里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They transport vast sums of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.80,0:24:31.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,传送到极远处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}down from the black hole out to huge distances,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.21,0:24:33.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许有百万光年之远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe about a million light-years or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.76,0:24:40.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,百万光年是我们银河系宽度的10倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A million light-years is 10 times wider than our Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.47,0:24:42.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着这些喷射强大到足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which means these jets are powerful enough
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.52,0:24:45.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生两个非常大的泡沫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to create two very big bubbles.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.27,0:24:54.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这两个泡沫的总能量大的惊人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The total energy within these two bubbles is stupendous,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.45,0:24:58.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远超过我们在宇宙间所知的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}far exceeding any other amount of concentrated energy 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.75,0:25:01.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何一种集束能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we know of in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.66,0:25:03.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎样 务必记住\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, it must be remembered
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.54,0:25:07.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量的释放已超过了100万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the energy was released over 100 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.17,0:25:10.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着每个单位时间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means that per unit of time
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.63,0:25:14.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所释放的总能量并不都是这么大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the total amount of energy released wasn't all that big.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.64,0:25:19.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 喷射还是强大到足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Still, the jets are strong enough
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.26,0:25:22.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以时速数百万英里把粒子射出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to shoot the particles out at millions of miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.14,0:25:24.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约为光速的四分之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about a quarter of the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.65,0:25:29.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射并产生泡沫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The jets and resulting bubbles 
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.10,0:25:34.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只出自宇宙中最庞大的黑洞的1%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only come from about 1% of the most massive black holes in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.40,0:25:38.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为这些怪物附近的力道非常大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's because the forces near these monsters are so huge
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.28,0:25:40.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是在吞噬一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that instead of swallowing everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.49,0:25:43.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是它们实际上最终在将一些粒子推得远远的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they actually end up pushing some particles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.66,0:25:49.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要强调的是 这些巨大的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's important to emphasize that these giant explosions
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.50,0:25:52.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并非黑洞本身的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are not the explosion of the black hole itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.75,0:25:56.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是粒子喷射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but rather an ejection of particles
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.51,0:26:00.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自附近的黑洞 周边的黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from near the black hole, the vicinity of the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.39,0:26:02.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过彼此碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By colliding with one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.51,0:26:07.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在某种情况下 它们可以被射出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can, in some cases, be ejected out of the vicinity
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.44,0:26:09.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,邻近的黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.02,0:26:14.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而如何才能让这种两面的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how can this two-sided blast
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.86,0:26:18.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能持续上亿年的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}possibly keep going for 100 million years?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.24,0:26:21.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关键在于有多少宇宙材料可供利用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's all a matter of how much cosmic stuff is available
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.53,0:26:24.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如行星 恒星被拉伸撕裂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as planets and suns are stretched and ripped apart
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.70,0:26:28.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至原子本身 并拽入黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}down to their very atoms and drawn towards the black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.59,0:26:34.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此这些喷射 我们估计已持续了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So these jets that we've estimated have been going on
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.05,0:26:36.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约1亿年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for about 100 million years
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.34,0:26:39.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,依然还有大量的燃料可供它们利用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}still have a huge amount of fuel available to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.51,0:26:42.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个过程可以继续很长的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That process can go on for an extremely long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.22,0:26:43.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数亿年之久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hundreds of millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.31,0:26:51.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在来想象一下 让大量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now imagine taking a big chunk of that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:53.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在两秒不到的时间释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and releasing it in less than two seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.90,0:26:58.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是研究人员认为在排名第4的爆炸中所发生的情景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what researchers believe happens in blast number 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.90,0:27:00.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,排名第4 - 短伽玛射线暴
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.57,0:27:07.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线暴比磁星爆发更为集束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gamma ray bursts are more concentrated than magnetar flares.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.45,0:27:11.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是辐射集束 宛如激光束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a concentrated beam of radiation, like a laser beam.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.00,0:27:15.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的出现就像是狭窄的射流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It comes out as a narrow stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.01,0:27:20.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,集束的伽玛射线的速度也远快于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gamma rays in the beams are also traveling much faster
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.51,0:27:23.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑洞喷射出的粒子流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the particles coming out of black hole jets.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.18,0:27:30.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观察表明 能量表现在射流里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The observations show that the energy is coming out in jets,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.27,0:27:32.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,速度接近光速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}moving at very close to the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.31,0:27:35.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,达到了光速的99 9999%\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}99.9999% the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.45,0:27:48.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以那个匪夷所思的速度就在短短的十分之几秒时间里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At that mind-bending speed, in just a few tenths of a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.16,0:27:50.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短伽玛射线暴能够释放出的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}short gamma ray bursts can release as much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.91,0:27:53.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于我们太阳数百万年里的释放量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as our Sun does in millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.75,0:27:58.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是多年来 科学家没能搞明白\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for years scientists couldn't figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.05,0:28:00.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为何有些伽玛射线暴是长的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why some gamma ray bursts were long,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.51,0:28:02.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,持续许多秒甚至几分钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lasting many seconds or even minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.88,0:28:06.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而其他的则通常只有若干分之一秒钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while others were usually only a fraction of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.47,0:28:08.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2005年的一个爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then one burst in 2005
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.89,0:28:11.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让研究人员有了一个令人兴奋的新理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}led researchers to an exciting new theory
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.64,0:28:16.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关于极其致密的中子星的相互湮灭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about incredibly dense neutron stars annihilating each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.40,0:28:23.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人造原子弹的威力相比宇宙间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The power of manmade atomic bombs is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.91,0:28:27.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,惊天动地的星系爆发来说 简直可以忽略不计了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to the galaxy-rattling explosions in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.70,0:28:30.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着我们继续倒数\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As we continue counting down
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.41,0:28:33.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中的10大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}10 of the biggest blasts in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.16,0:28:36.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些灾难性的事件现在产生的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}these cataclysmic events are now producing as much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.79,0:28:39.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都动辄就是我们太阳数以百万年计的量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as our Sun does in millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.42,0:28:44.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短伽玛射线暴为第4号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Short gamma ray bursts are number 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.01,0:28:50.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多年来 科学家一直对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For years, scientists have been confident
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.22,0:28:52.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长伽玛射线暴的源头了如指掌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the source of long gamma ray bursts,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.52,0:28:54.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是那些持续两秒钟以上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those that last over two seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.89,0:28:57.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至爆发许多分钟的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sometimes erupt for many minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.23,0:29:00.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们都是来自有大质量恒星的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They come from galaxies with massive stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.36,0:29:08.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某些大质量恒星死亡时 会塌缩爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when certain massive stars die, they collapse and then explode,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.41,0:29:13.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以集束伽玛射线喷射出巨量的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}blasting out incredible amounts of energy as concentrated jets of gamma rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.54,0:29:20.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在2005年 太空探测器捕捉到的强烈的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in 2005, detectors in space captured a powerful gamma ray burst
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.88,0:29:23.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只持续了一秒钟还不到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that only lasted for a fraction of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.76,0:29:27.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那令人非常激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was very exciting,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:30.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们以前所见到的伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because all the gamma ray bursts we'd seen before
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.10,0:29:31.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是完全不同的类型 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were of the different variety--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.51,0:29:35.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时间较长 出自有大量恒星在垂死挣扎的星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}longer, coming from galaxies where massive stars were dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.98,0:29:37.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个是不同的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.60,0:29:39.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它历时短暂 它所产生的区域里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was short, and it came from a region
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.02,0:29:42.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有大质量恒星的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where no massive stars existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.74,0:29:49.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个爆炸所产生的星系被认为存在着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This burst came from a galaxy thought to have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.24,0:29:52.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些极其致密的中子星 成双结对\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some incredibly dense neutron stars in binary pairs
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.83,0:29:54.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相互缠绕\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that orbit each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.00,0:29:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为产生如此快速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And scientists believe that the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.96,0:30:02.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和强劲的伽玛射线暴的唯一途径\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to generate such a quick and powerful burst of gamma rays
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.92,0:30:06.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是一旦两颗中子星卷入了致命的舞蹈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is if two neutron stars engage in a deadly dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.63,0:30:10.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相互围绕越来越亲近 最终会彼此撞在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbiting closer and closer, then finally crashing into each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.35,0:30:21.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时被认为是黑洞诞生的一刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is thought to be the moment when a black hole is born.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.82,0:30:25.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两颗中子星最终碰头时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the two neutron stars finally touch,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.11,0:30:28.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中的一颗中子星会被撕碎变成圆环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of the neutron stars gets shredded into a disc
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.45,0:30:31.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,剩余的部分已不足以成为中子星了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the thing that's left is too big to be a neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.12,0:30:34.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙间已没有什么力量能够容纳两颗中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no force in the universe that can hold up two neutron stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.70,0:30:37.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它就塌缩成了黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it collapses to a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.76,0:30:53.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2005年的事件 即所谓的GRB 050509b\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The 2005 event, known as GRB 050509b,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.14,0:30:55.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为第二次爆发发生在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since it was the second burst to occur
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.22,0:30:56.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那年的5月9日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on May 9th of that year,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.89,0:31:01.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首个短伽玛射线暴就被定位了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was the first short gamma ray burst whose location was pinned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.31,0:31:03.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球看来 它并不十分明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It didn't look very bright from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.52,0:31:08.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但那是因为它是在惊人的22亿光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that's because it was an astounding 2.2 billion light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.20,0:31:15.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,GRB 0509b只持续了约40毫秒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}GRB 0509b lasted only about 40 milliseconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.08,0:31:17.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而就在那段时间里 它所释放的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in that time, it released about as much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.00,0:31:20.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,达到了太阳在一亿年里的释放量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the Sun will release in a hundred million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.63,0:31:28.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是恒星碰撞的力量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the power of colliding stars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.76,0:31:32.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是无法与整个恒星从内部爆发所产生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can't compete with the even larger amount of energy released
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.72,0:31:36.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更大的量同日而语的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when an entire star explodes from the inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.44,0:31:48.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大恒星死亡时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When large stars die,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.36,0:31:51.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们并不会就像我们的太阳那样黯然退场\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they don't just fizzle out like our Sun eventually will.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.03,0:31:54.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们会在爆发中辞世\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They go out with a bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.41,0:32:00.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们其实有几种类型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are actually several types,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.71,0:32:03.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过超新星爆发的两种主要方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the two main ways a supernova explosion happens
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.88,0:32:06.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要么是双星系里的一颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is either when one star in a binary star system
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.88,0:32:09.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吞噬掉其伙伴的部分或全部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swallows part or all of its companion,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.96,0:32:13.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要么是超大质量恒星自身垮塌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or when a supermassive star collapses in on itself
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.76,0:32:16.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那个过程中将其外壳喷射出去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ejects its outer shell in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.51,0:32:23.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无论哪种方式 难以想象的能量被迅速释放出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Either way, a mind-boggling amount of energy is quickly released.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.77,0:32:31.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动能 喷射物质的动能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The energy of motion, the kinetic energy of the ejected material
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.57,0:32:34.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以相当于太阳在整个100亿年的生命周期里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can equal the total amount of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.53,0:32:39.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所释放的能量总和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the Sun will release over its entire 10-billion-year lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.42,0:32:49.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,双星型的超新星类似于氢弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The binary star type of supernova is similar to a hydrogen bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.80,0:32:53.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦核聚变失控就会导致大爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where runaway nuclear fusion leads to a massive explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.68,0:32:56.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些被称为1a型超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are known as Type 1a Supernovas,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.93,0:33:01.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2003年 其中的一个爆发涌进宇宙的光线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in 2003, one of these blasts flooded the cosmos with more light
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.02,0:33:05.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超过了众多恒星组成的整个星系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than an entire galaxy of stars combined.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.44,0:33:12.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它比太阳亮出了200亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was over 20 billion times more luminous than the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.24,0:33:13.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,持续了约两个星期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for about two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.61,0:33:17.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一切都来自某些物体的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this all came from the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.78,0:33:20.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它并不比月球大多少\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of something not much bigger than the Moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.08,0:33:22.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,质量约是太阳1 4倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 1.4 times the mass of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.87,0:33:25.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是一次热核爆炸 是核聚变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a thermonuclear explosion, from fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.63,0:33:32.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于核塌缩型超新星来说\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the core-collapse type of supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.09,0:33:34.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难以置信的能量产生在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an incredible amount of power is generated
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.55,0:33:36.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其外壳收缩 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the outer shell slams down 
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.40,0:33:40.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,受到了致密星核巨大的反冲力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gets an extra kick from the denser core of the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.93,0:33:46.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,试想这个乒乓球作为恒星外面的较轻的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine this ping-pong ball represents that outer, lighter material of the star,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.19,0:33:49.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而这个超级球作为较重的内核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whereas this super ball represents the heavy inner core.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.65,0:33:51.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以看到乒乓球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can see that the ping-pong ball
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.61,0:33:54.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上靠自身并不会弹跳很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually doesn't really bounce that much on its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.94,0:33:57.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是超级球的弹跳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there's the bounce of the super ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.78,0:34:01.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而你将看到的是 我把它们一起落下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what you'll see is that when I send them down together,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.62,0:34:05.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超级球的反弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the bounce of the super ball back up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.71,0:34:08.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会把乒乓球推得很高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will propel the ping-pong ball much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.34,0:34:15.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那非常像超新星里的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's very much like what happens in the supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.80,0:34:19.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里 你有较重的内核向外反弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where you have the heavy inner core bouncing back out
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.18,0:34:21.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遇上较轻的物质 将其炸出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and meeting that lighter material and blowing it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.14,0:34:32.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 2005年的一颗超新星爆发 即SN 2005ap\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, one supernova explosion in 2005, known as SN 2005ap,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.32,0:34:36.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数周内一直就比其他恒星更加闪亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flashed brighter than all of the others for weeks on end.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.57,0:34:38.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过它并没有给地球带来任何伤害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it didn't do any damage to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.61,0:34:43.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为 庆幸的是 它也是在47亿光年之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because, luckily, it was also 4.7 billion light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.95,0:34:48.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和头10位的其它排名一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And like many of the other blasts on the top 10 list,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.00,0:34:51.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星并不只是破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}supernovas don't just destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.67,0:35:00.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超新星有点像回收中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova is a little bit like a recycling center.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.89,0:35:03.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些超大质量恒星有大量的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a lot of material in those massive stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.22,0:35:10.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其质量是我们太阳的8倍到100多倍不等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's anything from eight times to over a hundred times the mass of our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.56,0:35:11.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此有大量的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's a lot of material
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.65,0:35:13.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会在那些恒星中得到处理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's going to be processed in those stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.94,0:35:16.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宛如有大量的材料在回收中心这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just like there's a lot of raw material here at the recycling center
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.90,0:35:18.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进行处理一般\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's going to be processed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.07,0:35:25.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙中的元素以轻元素为主\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The matter in the universe is dominated by light elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.58,0:35:27.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如氢和氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like hydrogen and helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.29,0:35:30.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是即将成为超新星的恒星内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the inside of a star about to go supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.62,0:35:32.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是伴随我们终身的各种金属\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the main source of the various metals
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.54,0:35:35.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,及其它重元素的主要来源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other heavy elements we depend on for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.50,0:35:39.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像这些材料被分类成不同的类别\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just like these materials are being sorted into different categories,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:42.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星也在着手处理着越来越重的元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star starts to process heavier and heavier elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.43,0:35:44.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始是氢 接着是氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}starting with hydrogen, then helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.93,0:35:47.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,制造着越来越重的元素 一直到铁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making heavier and heavier elements all the way up to iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.77,0:35:49.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时聚变过程终告结束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the fusion process stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.98,0:35:52.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在其成为超新星后 继续着它的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Later on in its life when it becomes supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.77,0:35:55.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,借助于超新星的挤压效应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the aid of the compression effect in the supernova,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.48,0:35:57.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恒星会制造出更加重的元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the star will make even heavier elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.53,0:36:02.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像这些材料被打包处理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as these materials are now packaged and processed
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.95,0:36:04.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,准备离开回收中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ready to leave the recycling center
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.95,0:36:07.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出去重新使用一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and go out into the world to be reused,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.29,0:36:09.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产自恒星的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the materials that were made in the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.00,0:36:13.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终会被经过超新星的加工调制\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that were then finally cooked and blown out into the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.50,0:36:15.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,炸入宇宙中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the supernova process,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.29,0:36:17.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也将被重新使用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those will be reused as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.21,0:36:21.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们可能被其他恒星甚至其他行星利用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They may be used in other stars or perhaps other planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.22,0:36:23.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,构成我们地球的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The materials that we're made of here on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.43,0:36:25.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至我们身体的材料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the materials even in our bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.64,0:36:28.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些重元素都是超新星制造的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those heavy elements were made in supernovae.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.65,0:36:38.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然超新星本身就是巨大的爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While supernovas are massive explosions themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.32,0:36:43.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它们还能用更为集中的能量触发二次爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can also trigger secondary blasts with even more concentrated energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.74,0:36:51.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The long gamma ray burst
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.16,0:36:54.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出自最强烈的超新星爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes out of the most powerful supernova explosions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.83,0:36:57.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们强如短伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're as strong as the short gamma ray bursts,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.50,0:36:59.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是由于它们持续时间更长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but since they last much longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.67,0:37:02.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会从2秒到近半小时不等\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}anywhere from two seconds to nearly half an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.84,0:37:05.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们总体上爆发出更多的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they blast out much more energy overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.72,0:37:09.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长伽玛射线暴相对短伽玛射线暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The long gamma ray bursts are completely different beasts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.39,0:37:10.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是完全不同的巨兽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to the short gamma ray bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.85,0:37:11.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们更加强烈无比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're immensely more powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.02,0:37:15.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许会比短期爆发强烈1万倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe up to around 10,000 times more powerful than the short-duration bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.69,0:37:22.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些超新星爆发所产生的集束能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These concentrated jets of energy only come from supernova explosions
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.07,0:37:26.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只涉及那些质量是我们太阳的30倍乃至更多的恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}involving stars 30 or more times the mass of our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.61,0:37:28.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像短伽玛射线暴那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And just like the short gamma ray bursts,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.82,0:37:31.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是黑洞诞生的证据\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're evidence of the birth of a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.70,0:37:36.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长伽玛射线暴在某种意义上是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Long gamma ray bursts are, in some sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.08,0:37:39.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种超能超新星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a variety of hyper-energetic supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.50,0:37:43.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,铁核塌缩 如前所述 会成为中子星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The iron core collapses, as before, to a neutron star,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.05,0:37:45.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有太多的材料塌缩进去的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but too much material falls down on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.51,0:37:48.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是不能停留在中子星上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it can't stay a neutron star.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.39,0:37:50.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度会升至100亿度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The temperature rises to 10 billion degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.51,0:37:54.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其一立方英寸的亮度会大如太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The luminosity in one cubic inch of this is as big as the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.73,0:37:57.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种能量是无法从赤道上流出的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this power can't flow out on the equator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.27,0:37:59.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它经过了聚焦 就像是猎枪发射一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It gets focused, like in a shotgun blast,
